#: src/pages/Status.tsx
#~ msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h, with a luck multiplier comparing observed vs expected. Reads exactly count/expected at the moment of every find (e.g. 2 found vs 3.45 expected = 0.58×); decays continuously between finds (the longer we go without a block, the unluckier we look). At Ocean's ~5% share of network hashrate the expected count is ~7 blocks/24h. Same number the chart's right-axis pool-luck line plots. Wide variance is normal at 24h."
#~ msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h, with a luck multiplier comparing observed vs expected. Reads exactly count/expected at the moment of every find (e.g. 2 found vs 3.45 expected = 0.58×); decays continuously between finds (the longer we go without a block, the unluckier we look). At Ocean's ~5% share of network hashrate the expected count is ~7 blocks/24h. Same number the chart's right-axis pool-luck line plots. Wide variance is normal at 24h."

#: src/pages/Status.tsx
#~ msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The 'X.XX× lucky/unlucky' annotation compares observed vs the network-share expectation: at Ocean's ~5% share of network hashrate and ~144 blocks/day on the network, the expected count is ~7 blocks/24h. 1.00× = exactly that; >1 = lucky; <1 = unlucky. Wide variance is normal at 24h (Poisson σ is large at this window); the 7d row below is where sustained drift becomes meaningful."
#~ msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The 'X.XX× lucky/unlucky' annotation compares observed vs the network-share expectation: at Ocean's ~5% share of network hashrate and ~144 blocks/day on the network, the expected count is ~7 blocks/24h. 1.00× = exactly that; >1 = lucky; <1 = unlucky. Wide variance is normal at 24h (Poisson σ is large at this window); the 7d row below is where sustained drift becomes meaningful."

#: src/pages/Status.tsx
msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier compares observed vs Poisson-expected. Pool hashrate / network difficulty unavailable right now; tooltip will show live share % once Ocean stats are reachable again."
msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier compares observed vs Poisson-expected. Pool hashrate / network difficulty unavailable right now; tooltip will show live share % once Ocean stats are reachable again."

#: src/pages/Status.tsx
#~ msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier is the observed rate divided by the Poisson-derived expected rate: at Ocean's ~5% share of network hashrate, the expectation is ~144 × 5% = ~7 blocks/24h. The denominator extends with elapsed-since-last-block so the value decays continuously between finds; at the moment of each find it equals exactly count / expected_for_window. >1.00× means we found more than expected, <1.00× means fewer. Same number the chart's right-axis pool-luck line plots. Wide variance is normal at 24h - Poisson σ is large at this window."
#~ msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier is the observed rate divided by the Poisson-derived expected rate: at Ocean's ~5% share of network hashrate, the expectation is ~144 × 5% = ~7 blocks/24h. The denominator extends with elapsed-since-last-block so the value decays continuously between finds; at the moment of each find it equals exactly count / expected_for_window. >1.00× means we found more than expected, <1.00× means fewer. Same number the chart's right-axis pool-luck line plots. Wide variance is normal at 24h - Poisson σ is large at this window."

#. placeholder {0}: fmt(expected24h, 2)
#: src/pages/Status.tsx
msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier is the observed rate divided by the Poisson-derived expected rate: Ocean's current share of network hashrate is {shareStr}, so the expectation over 24h (~144 blocks on the network) is ~{0} blocks. The denominator extends with elapsed-since-last-block so the value decays continuously between finds; at the moment of each find it equals exactly count / expected_for_window. >1.00× means we found more than expected, <1.00× means fewer. Same number the chart's right-axis pool-luck line plots. Wide variance is normal at 24h - Poisson σ is large at this window."
msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier is the observed rate divided by the Poisson-derived expected rate: Ocean's current share of network hashrate is {shareStr}, so the expectation over 24h (~144 blocks on the network) is ~{0} blocks. The denominator extends with elapsed-since-last-block so the value decays continuously between finds; at the moment of each find it equals exactly count / expected_for_window. >1.00× means we found more than expected, <1.00× means fewer. Same number the chart's right-axis pool-luck line plots. Wide variance is normal at 24h - Poisson σ is large at this window."

#: src/pages/Status.tsx
#~ msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 7d, same formula as the 24h row. 7d smooths the short-term variance: a sustained <0.7× over a week suggests something structural (lower hashrate share than the estimator implies, or a real upstream issue at Ocean)."
#~ msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 7d, same formula as the 24h row. 7d smooths the short-term variance: a sustained <0.7× over a week suggests something structural (lower hashrate share than the estimator implies, or a real upstream issue at Ocean)."

